<br>
Right click the merchant to bring up a list of stuff they sell. Then click on your items (left button) and they will tell you how much they will pay for it.<br>
<br>
If the list of stuff they sell doesnt print up, go find someone else.<br>
<br>
Truthfully, I wouldn't reccomend a mage as a starting character, they are kind of a pain as you need to learn 20 things at once. I would play a melee class to start. Early in the game, a melee class is very straightforward, and you are really just trying to learn how the world works, not to level your character to 65 as fast as you can.<br>
<br>
As for items, I believe you have dropped them on your &quot;paper doll&quot; model correctly. The reason you don't see it, is most low end gear you find like cloth or tattered silk has no graphic. Your newbie (beginner) robe will have a graphic, I think High Elves get a purple robe, but don't remember perfectly.  As you get further along, you will be able to see more of your gear, as higher end items tend to have more distinctive graphics.<br>
<br>
What server do you play on? I am sure some folks who live there wouldn't mind helping you out.<br>
<br>
